bob
Homonym Number:  2
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:orig. worms threaded and coiled (see cit. 1967), but also meat, bacon, etc. held in a tangle of twine or shredded flax-blade, attached to a line, for catching eels.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1940 a bob of tangled bindertwine, or flax, holding a bait for eels whose backward-sloping teeth would become entangled allowing them to be dragged from the water
Citations
