Source:  First White Boy Born in Otago
Author:  BEATTIE
Vol / Page:  16
Edition:
Quote:  The white man always tries to catch eels with a bob or hook, but when I was a boy I saw the Maoris get them in eel baskets ...
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1967
Source:  Tang of The Bush
Author:  KEENE
Vol / Page:  103
Edition:
Quote:  With a darning needle and thread, ... they soon had a [104] five foot string of worms which they coiled into a bob and tied in several places. This was fastened with flax to a strong stick about six feet long. [early 20C.] We went down to the river about dusk, each of us with a rod, ... our bobs suspended in a deep pool.
